[00:00.000]--- Lesson 47  A thirsty ghost 嗜酒的鬼魂
[00:04.493]A public house which was recently bought by Mr. Ian Thompson is up for sale.^伊恩.汤普森先生最近才买的一个小酒店现在又要卖出去。
[00:12.069]Mr. Thompson is going to sell it because it is haunted.^汤普森先生之所以想卖它，是因为那里常闹鬼。
[00:17.424]He told me that he could not go to sleep one night because he heard a strange noise coming from the bar.^他告诉我有天夜里他怎么也睡不着，因为他听到酒吧里传来一阵奇怪的响声。
[00:26.149]The next morning, he found that the doors had been blocked by chairs and the furniture had been moved.^第二天早上，他发现酒吧间的门被椅子堵上了，家具也被挪动过。
[00:34.273]Though Mr. Thompson had turned the lights off before he went to bed, they were on in the morning.^虽然汤普森临睡觉时把灯关了，但早晨灯却都亮着。
[00:42.658]He also said that he had found five empty whisky bottles which the ghost must have drunk the night before.^他还说他发现了5只空的威士忌酒瓶子，这肯定是鬼魂昨天晚上喝的。
[00:52.140]When I suggested that some villagers must have come in for a free drink, Mr. Thompson shook his head.^当我暗示说一定是村里有些人来喝不花钱的酒时，汤普森先生摇了摇头。
[01:01.832]The villagers have told him that they will not accept the pub even if he gives it away.^村里的人已经告诉他，即使他把小酒店白送人，他们也不要。
